<HEADLINE>
FT  25 MAR 94 / Record profit of Pounds 5.6m at ITN
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Independent Television News achieved its largest pre-tax profit last year -
Pounds 5.6m before exceptional items on a turnover of Pounds 83.3m, Raymond
Snoddy writes.
The figure represents a considerable turnaround for the commercial
television news organisation. Three years ago there was a cost overrun of
Pounds 10m and a growing financial crisis because of lease charges on its
then new headquarters in Gray's Inn Road, London.
There had been fears that the loss on the lease on the near-empty building
could reach Pounds 25m over five years. But the building has been filling up
slowly, mainly with media organisations.
The latest tenant is The European newspaper which plans to move from Orbit
House, part of the former Maxwell empire.
