would probably end up with nothing.
Trizec, hit by the property market collapse in North America, and with
insufficient cashflow to service debt, said its primary aim was to have a
recapitalisation plan accepted so the company could survive intact.
Abitibi-Price, the North American pulp and paper group, plans to raise
CDollars 173.5m of new equity next month with a public issue of common stock
at Dollars 17.35 a share.
The proceeds will be used for capital projects, debt refinancing and working
capital.
