<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 94 / Prescott says Labour must focus on redistribution of work as
well as wealth
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART and ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Labour party will have to focus on redistribution of work as much as
redistribution of wealth, Mr John Prescott, shadow employment secretary,
said yesterday, David Goodhart and Robert Taylor write.
Mr Prescott said the market was distributing work unsatisfactorily between
the employed and the unemployed and between full-time and part-time workers.
In recent years 3m full-time jobs had been replaced by 1.5m part-time and
1.5m self-employed.
Since taking over as Labour employment spokesman after the party conference
last year, Mr Prescott has had a relatively low profile on labour market
issues - with the exception of harrying the government on the issue of
unemployment statistics. However, new thinking on the subject will come with
the publication of the party's response to the European Commission's green
paper on social policy published at the end of last year.
The response, under the title Jobs and Social Justice, is likely to further
Mr Prescott's reputation as a moderniser in traditionalist clothing.
The Labour document is likely to concentrate on establishing new links
between employment and social security to take account of changes in working
and family lives. Mr Prescott says new thinking on the Continent is coming
from 'the Keyneses and Beveridges of our time'.
</TEXT>
<XX>
