<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 94 / More staff cuts at Alliance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Alliance &amp; Leicester building society yesterday announced that it is to shed
up to 550 jobs, almost all before the end of next year, as part of its
restructuring, which includes integration of personal customers of its
Girobank subsidiary with those of the society.
Mr Paul Clifton, director in charge of human resources, said the effect
would be felt in administration, where the group wanted to flatten its
management structures. The aim is to ensure that it can make faster
decisions.
The job losses come on top of an announcement last November that about 700
jobs would be lost over the next four years as a result of the closure of
the society's headquarters in Hove. Mr Clifton said he did not expect any
further job losses as a result of the organisational review.
Mr Clifton said he regretted the job losses, but tight control over costs
was essential.
</TEXT>
