<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 94 / Unit trust sales up 50% to Pounds 722m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SCHEHERAZADE DANESHKHU
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Unit trusts sales of Pounds 722.4m last month were almost 50 per cent higher
than in January and compared with Pounds 580.5m in February last year,
Scheherazade Daneshkhu writes.
Retail demand has again been heavy, with almost three quarters of last
month's net sales - Pounds 530m - made by private investors. Many savers
have been turning to equities as an alternative to building societies at a
time of relatively low interest rates.
Last week the Building Societies Association reported net outflow of funds
of Pounds 404m after a net outflow of Pounds 265m in January.
The most popular sectors with private investors were the five UK equity fund
sectors which attracted a net Pounds 335m of investment. UK and European
funds qualify for full Personal Equity Plan allowances, which allow
individuals to invest in equities tax-efficiently. The best-selling sector
among private investors were the international growth funds.
Institutions favoured Japan and there was a shift away from the 'Far East
excluding Japan sector' into 'Far East including Japan' funds.
</TEXT>
