FT  24 MAR 94 / Big Four pension managers dominate
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NORMA COHEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The so-called Big Four UK pension fund managers outperformed the average in
1993, but by a far smaller margin than in recent years, Combined Actuarial
Performance Services, which measures pension fund manager returns, reported
yesterday, Norma Cohen writes.
The four are Mercury Asset Management, Schroders Investment Management, PDFM
and Gartmore. The Big Four earned total returns on their portfolios,
exclusive of property investments, of 29.3 per cent. The median market
return was 29.3 per cent. But in the five year period 1989 through 1993, the
Big Four earned median returns of 18 per cent per year while the median
return was 17.2 per cent.
