FT  24 MAR 94 / Labour 'would take back coal pits'
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IVOR OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The next Labour government would renationalise coal mines if that was what
mineworkers wanted, Mr Robin Cook, shadow trade and industry secretary, told
the Commons last night, Ivor Owen writes.
Responding to a challenge from Mr Patrick McLoughlin, a junior minister, Mr
Cook said he would be 'astonished' if Labour's plans for rescuing the coal
industry did not involve public ownership.
Mr Dennis Skinner, leftwing Labour MP for Bolsover who is sponsored by the
National Union of Mineworkers, described this as 'a big improvement'.
A Labour attempt to prevent the closure of any more pits before the
establishment of the new Coal Authority provided for by the coal industry
bill was defeated by 31.
