<HEADLINE>
FT  24 MAR 94 / GDP set to rise in NZ
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TERRY HALL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WELLINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The New Zealand Reserve Bank yesterday forecast that gross domestic product
would rise by 5.3 per cent in the year to March, with growth tapering off to
an average of 3.5 per cent over the next two years, writes Terry Hall in
Wellington. Inflation was expected to remain well within the zero to 2 per
cent range.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>NZZ  New Zealand.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P9311 Finance, Taxation, and Monetary Policy.
</IN>
<XX>
