FT  24 MAR 94 / Japan motor output falls
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL ABRAHAMS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Japan's motor industry output fell 14.1 per cent in February against the
same period last year, the 17th consecutive monthly fall, writes Paul
Abrahams in Tokyo. The industry's performance underlines the depth of the
recession. Output of cars, trucks and buses fell to 896,000 units, the sixth
month in which the decline has been in double digits, a post-war record.
