FT  24 MAR 94 / Kohl welcomes Major proposal on German participation in
D-Day celebrations
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Our Foreign Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Chancellor Helmut Kohl has warmly welcomed a proposal from Britain's prime
minister, Mr John Major, to invite high-level German participation next year
at 50th anniversary celebrations in London of the end of the Second World
War, Our Foreign Staff writes. The British leader's invitation appears to be
an attempt to defuse a gathering diplomatic row over British and French
reluctance to invite the German chancellor to celebrate the 50th anniversary
of the Normandy landings. Referring to a possible visit to the UK, he said
it could be done in a 'good and dignified manner'.
