<HEADLINE>
FT  23 MAR 94 / China's inflation rate rises
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Foreign Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Figures indicating a rise in China's inflation rate were published in the
Chinese press yesterday, our Foreign Staff writes. The reports said retail
prices in the first two months rose 20 per cent nationwide over the same
period last year, against 13 per cent for all of 1993. The State Statistical
Bureau report showed industrial output grew by 18.2 per cent in the first
two months; capital construction surged 41.8 per cent in the same period.
